Also, the decline was partly due to the termination of state support programs, in particular, the car recycling program. Sales in the Russian market this year amounted to 537.6 thousand cars, and taking into account exports, 608.2 thousand. In April 2012, AvtoVAZ began production of Lada Largus station wagons - cars created on the B0 platform provided by the Renault-Nissan Alliance.[67]
At the end of 2013, the enterprise and its site in Izhevsk produced 516.3 thousand vehicles.